  "slug": "what-does-good-enough-with-my-body-look-like",
  "title": "What Does Good Enough with My Body Look Like?",
  "subtitle": "A journal prompt set for releasing all-or-nothing body thinking",
  "excerpt": "A set of six journal prompts for when the body relationship is stuck in all-or-nothing. The prompts move from a broad orienting question toward a specific picture of what a workable relationship with the body actually looks like for you.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 9 of WEIGHT LOSS: A 12-Week Tapping Program (Rebecca J Page, 2025).",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A journal prompt set for the all-or-nothing body relationship. The binary of \"doing everything\" or \"having blown it\" leaves no room for a middle that most people can actually live in.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journalling as a practice? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where is the all-or-nothing in my body relationship right now?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write the specific version of it. Not \"I'm all-or-nothing\" in general but the thing that split last week, or this morning.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does \"perfect\" look like in this scenario?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write out the standard you're holding yourself to. Get it on paper so you can look at it.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does \"good enough\" with my body actually look like?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Not ideal. Not minimal. The version that is liveable, repeatable, and yours.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where in my body relationship am I already at \"good enough\"?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Name one specific thing you do consistently that counts.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Who taught me that partial counts as nothing?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where did the binary come from? A parent, a diet, a decade?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What would change if some-of-the-time counted?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write what your week would look like if partial effort still added up.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Adapted from Day 9 of WEIGHT LOSS: A 12-Week Tapping Program (Rebecca J Page, 2025).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
